## Root layout (Backend/ and Frontend/ sub-folders)

**Path:** `Cursor-Project/test_cases/`

Test case files are organized in **two sub-folders** by testing layer:

| Folder | Contents | Required? |
|--------|----------|-----------|
| **Backend/** | Backend (API) test cases — `TC-BE-N`. One `.md` file per topic. | **ALWAYS** |
| **Frontend/** | Frontend (UI) test cases — `TC-FE-N`. One `.md` file per topic. | **Only if user confirmed** |

**Path patterns:**
- `test_cases/Backend/<Topic_name>.md` — contains only **Backend Test Cases** (`TC-BE-N`). **ALWAYS created.**
- `test_cases/Frontend/<Topic_name>.md` — contains only **Frontend Test Cases** (`TC-FE-N`). **Created ONLY if user answered "Yes" to Frontend question.**

- **&lt;Topic_name&gt;** = descriptive name for the task, bug, feature, or flow being tested. Use underscores for multi-word names.
- The Backend file MUST NOT contain Frontend test cases, and vice versa.

**Examples (when user chose "Yes" for Frontend):**
- `test_cases/Backend/Invoice_cancellation.md` + `test_cases/Frontend/Invoice_cancellation.md`
- `test_cases/Backend/Product_contract_create.md` + `test_cases/Frontend/Product_contract_create.md`

**Examples (when user chose "No" — Backend only):**
- `test_cases/Backend/Invoice_cancellation.md` (NO Frontend file created)
- `test_cases/Backend/Product_contract_create.md` (NO Frontend file created)

**Do NOT create an empty Frontend file with "N/A" note** when user chose "No" — simply do not create the file.

